description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Alder Hey in the Park:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Have you ever wanted to work in a hospital built entirely in a park with a design inspired by children? As a member of the bank you can work alongside the hospitals’ experienced staff in the new ‘Alder Hey in the Park’ hospital which boasts spacious wards, improved clinic areas, advanced research facilities and fantastic areas in which young people can play and relax.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Joining NHS Professionals to work at &lt;strong&gt;Alder Hey Children’s Hospital&lt;/strong&gt; gives you total flexibility to pick up shifts when it’s convenient for you. Long day shifts and night shifts (as well as flexible hours upon request) are available across the Trust’s medical, surgical and other specialities; so there is plenty of opportunity for you to earn extra money and develop your experience in one of the largest paediatric hospitals in Europe!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;We have a ongoing post for all shifts at the Trust.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Location is commutable from Liverpool, Wirral, Warrington, Widnes, Runcorn, Ormskirk etc.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Band 5:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Day £22.76 / Night &amp; Sat £29.59 / Sun &amp; BH £36.42&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Summary:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;In order to apply for this post you should have a minimum &lt;strong&gt;of six months experience&lt;/strong&gt; within an acute paediatric setting, ideally gained within the last two years, but not essential. You will be accountable for the following duties:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working as the primary nurse, ensuring the delivery of a high standard of care for patients and families&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Centred assessment and treatment plans as agreed with the multidisciplinary team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utilising basic analytical skills as required to enhance the patients development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Observing, communicating and at times co-working with senior multidisciplinary team members in the provision of a range of therapeutic approaches on an individual, group or family basis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Providing high quality clear written and verbal accounts of the patients stay in relation to defined care and management plans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contributing to evidence-based clinical nursing reports, for parents and multi-disciplinary professionals as agreed with the core team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supporting and adhering to related policies and protocols.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;In return for your hard work and caring skills, we can offer you some fantastic benefits: –&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Competitive Pay Rates - &lt;/strong&gt;work this week, get paid next week!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;·&lt;/span&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Build holiday allowance for every shift you work &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Support when you need it – 24/7 365 days – &lt;/strong&gt;Call us anytime on 03332 407 552&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Stakeholder pension scheme&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Who are NHS Professionals?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;NHS Professionals (NHSP), owned by the Department of Health and Social Care (DHSC), works in partnership with hospital trusts to provide a bank of highly skilled temporary workers who want to work flexibly within the NHS. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Working through the NHSP bank means Trusts don’t have to rely on expensive agencies. Right now, we have over 126,000 members registered on our bank from various roles, grades and specialities, saving the NHS over &lt;strong&gt;£70 million&lt;/strong&gt; each year. This money is then reinvested back into the NHS. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Apply &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please visit NHS Jobs website to complete your application. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For more information on the roles or details on how to join NHS Professionals, simply get in touch with&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; Doreen Innes, Trust Recruitment Coordinator, on 07917193246 or &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;alderhey@nhsprofessionals.nhs.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; .&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We look forward to hearing from you soon. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Disclaimer &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please note, you will be contacted by email throughout the recruitment process, so please check your emails, including your junk/spam regularly. We regret we cannot contact everyone who is not selected for an interview, therefore if you do not hear from us within 21 days after submitting your application, please assume you have not been successful on this occasion. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
